'''Hwang In-beom''' ({{langx|ko|황인범}}; born 20 September 1996) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for
[[Eredivisie]] club [[Feyenoord]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Club career==
=== Daejeon Citizen ===
Hwang signed with [[Daejeon Hana Citizen|Daejeon Citizen]] in 2015. He scored his first goal in a league match against [[Pohang Steelers]] on 30 May and became the youngest scorer in Daejeon history.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201506020100012170000538&servicedate=20150601 |script-title=ko:유스 출신' 황인범, 대전 시티즌 '최연소 득점' 기록세워 |publisher=[[Sports Chosun]] |date=1 June 2015|language=ko}}</ref> Daejeon had been relegated to the second division after his first season, but he grew into one of notable young footballers in South Korea.

Hwang joined police's football team [[Asan Mugunghwa FC|Asan Mugunghwa]] to perform alternative service instead of mandatory military service in 2018, but was discharged from the service after winning a gold medal in the [[Football at the 2018 Asian Games|2018 Asian Games]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.mt.co.kr/mtview.php?no=2018090409031337570 |script-title=ko:'일경 황인범' AG 금메달로 조기전역…군복무 9개월로 끝 |publisher={{ill|Money Today|ko|머니투데이}} |language=ko |date=2018-09-04 |access-date=2023-09-04}}</ref>

=== Vancouver Whitecaps FC ===
Hwang interested [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[Hamburger SV]] after showing positive prospects in Daejeon and national team, but Daejeon sold Hwang to [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] who offered a higher transfer fee than Hamburg.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.taegukwarriors.com/hwang-in-beom-and-family-angry-over-derailed-transfer-to-hamburg-by-shady-agent/ |title=Hwang In-beom and family angry over derailed transfer to Hamburg by "shady" agent [UPDATE 2.15] |publisher=Taeguk Warriors |date=12 February 2019 |access-date=30 July 2022}}</ref> On 30 January 2019, Hwang joined [[Major League Soccer]] side Vancouver Whitecaps as a Young [[Designated Player Rule|Designated Player]] on a two-year contract, with club options for the 2021 and 2022 seasons.<ref name="Hwang" >{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/post/2019/01/30/whitecaps-fc-acquire-south-korean-international-hwang-in-beom|title=Whitecaps FC acquire South Korean international midfielder Hwang In-beom|publisher=Vancouver Whitecaps FC|date=30 January 2019}}</ref> He made his debut for the Whitecaps against [[Minnesota United]] on 2 March,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dailyhive.com/vancouver/whitecaps-fc-mls-season-opener-2019|date=2 March 2019|title=9 players make Whitecaps debut in MLS season opener|first=Mark|last=Dailey}}</ref> and scored his first goal for the side in a 1–0 win over [[Los Angeles FC]] on 17 April.<ref>{{Cite web| title=Whitecaps top LAFC for 1st win of season| first=Gemma |last=Karstens-Smith| publisher=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation| date=18 April 2019| access-date=18 April 2019| url=https://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/mls/mls-vancouver-whitecaps-los-angeles-fc-recap-april-17-1.5103068}}</ref> In the 30th week of the [[2019 Major League Soccer season|2019 season]], he was selected for the Team of the Week after providing three assists against [[LA Galaxy]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/hwang-named-mls-team-week-following-three-assist-performance |title=Hwang named to MLS Team of the Week following three-assist performance |publisher=Vancouver Whitecaps FC |date=1 October 2019 |access-date=30 July 2022}}</ref>

=== Rubin Kazan ===
[[File:Hwang In-beom 2020.jpg|thumb|upright|Hwang with [[FC Rubin Kazan|Rubin Kazan]] in 2020]]
On 14 August 2020, Hwang transferred to Russian club [[FC Rubin Kazan|Rubin Kazan]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.rubin-kazan.ru/posts/hvan-in-bom-v-rubine |title=ХВАН ИН БОМ – В "РУБИНЕ" |publisher=Rubin Kazan |date=14 August 2020 |access-date=14 August 2020 |language=ru |archive-date=15 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815212045/https://www.rubin-kazan.ru/posts/hvan-in-bom-v-rubine |url-status=dead }}</ref> Hwang ranked favorably in statistics for chances created across the [[Russian Premier League]] until the first half of the 2020–21 season,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://t.me/markstats/341 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20201222023451/https://t.me/markstats/341#selection-137.0-139.76 |title=Игроки Российской Премьер-Лиги, которые создают наибольшее количество голевых моментов для партнеров. |language=ru |author=Markstats |archive-date=22 December 2020 |date=24 November 2020}}</ref> but suffered [[SARS-CoV-2|coronavirus]] and heel injury afterward.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.hani.co.kr/arti/sports/soccer/969926.html |script-title=ko:벤투호 비상…권창훈·이동준·조현우·황인범 코로나19 양성 |publisher=[[The Hankyoreh]] |date=14 November 2020 |language=ko |access-date=30 July 2022}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/sports_photo/2021/03/09/SLN5BU72WSL4T4IA6QUNUPV5MU/ |script-title=ko:보호기는 풀었지만…아킬레스건 부상 황인범,4월께 복귀 전망 |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |date=9 March 2021 |language=ko |access-date=30 July 2022}}</ref>

On 3 April 2022, Hwang's contract with Rubin was suspended until 30 June 2022 according to special FIFA regulations related to the [[2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine|Russian invasion of Ukraine]]. The regulations allow foreign players in Russia to suspend their contracts until the end of the 2021–22 season and sign with a club outside of Russia until that date.<ref>{{cite press release|publisher=[[FC Rubin Kazan]]|url=https://rubin-kazan.ru/posts/in-bom-hvan-priostanovil-kontrakt-s-rubinom|title=ИН БОМ ХВАН ПРИОСТАНОВИЛ КОНТРАКТ С "РУБИНОМ"|date=3 April 2022|language=ru|access-date=3 April 2022|archive-date=3 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220703152909/https://www.rubin-kazan.ru/posts/in-bom-hvan-priostanovil-kontrakt-s-rubinom|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FIFA]]|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/organisation/fifa-council/media-releases/fifa-adopts-temporary-employment-and-registration-rules-to-address-several|title=FIFA adopts temporary employment and registration rules to address several issues in relation to war in Ukraine|date=7 March 2022}}</ref> Hwang joined [[FC Seoul]] on 5 April.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Seoul]]|url=https://www.fcseoul.com/media/newsView?seq=3999&resultPart=News|title=FC서울, 국가대표 미드필더 황인범 영입|date=5 April 2022|language=ko}}</ref>

=== Olympiacos ===
On 29 July 2022, Hwang joined [[Super League Greece]] club [[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 July 2022 |title=Στον Ολυμπιακό ο Ίνμπομ Χουάνγκ |url=https://www.olympiacos.org/2022/07/29/ston-olympiako-o-inmpom-xouangk/ |access-date=29 July 2022 |website=ΟΛΥΜΠΙΑΚΟΣ - Olympiacos.org |language=el}}</ref> On 18 August 2022, he scored, on his debut, the equaliser in a [[Europa League play-offs|Europa League playoff]] fixture away at [[Apollon Limassol FC|Apollon Limassol]], which finished 1–1.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Apollon-Olympiacos {{!}} Stats {{!}} UEFA Europa League 2022/23 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2035499--apollon-vs-olympiacos/statistics/ |access-date=18 August 2022 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref> On 10 March 2023, he was named the [[2022–23 Super League Greece#MVP Month|Super League Greece Player of the Month]] for February.<ref name="potm">{{cite news |url=https://www.slgr.gr/el/article/stoiximan-player-of-the-month-tou-phebrouariou-o-inmpom-khouangk/ |title=Stoiximan Player of the Month του Φεβρουαρίου o Ίνμπομ Χουάνγκ |publisher=Super League Greece |language=el |date=2023-03-10 |access-date=2023-03-30}}</ref> After the end of the 2022–23 season, he was selected as the best Olympiacos player and the second best Super League Greece player by league fans.<ref name="potc">{{Cite web |title=Stoiximan Player Of The Club του Ολυμπιακού ο Ίνμπομ Χουάνγκ |url=https://www.slgr.gr/el/article/stoiximan-player-of-the-club-tou-olumpiakou-o-inmpom-khouangk/ |date=2023-06-12 |access-date=2023-06-15 |publisher=Super League Greece |language=el}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.slgr.gr/el/article/stoiximan-player-of-the-season-2022-23-o-ormpelin-pineda/ |title=Stoiximan Player of the Season 2022-23 ο Ορμπελίν Πινέδα |publisher=Super League Greece |language=el |date=2023-06-30 |access-date=2023-08-15}}</ref> However, he was in conflict with the club just before the next season due to problems related to his contract, and it was possible to become a court fight. He claimed he held a one-year contract with an option for a further two years, whereas Olympiacos claimed a three-year deal.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/english/kpop-culture-en/2023/09/06/NZ33DKRYZHE722RRY4ZFST4LZE/ |title=Hwang In-beom Signs 4-Year Deal with Top Serbian Club |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |date=2023-09-06 |access-date=2024-08-30}}</ref>

=== Red Star Belgrade ===
On 4 September 2023, Hwang joined [[Serbian SuperLiga]] club [[Red Star Belgrade]] on a four-year contract for a club and league-record €5 million fee. He was bought along with [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkinabè]] centre-back [[Nasser Djiga]] and [[Senegal national football team|Senegalese]] winger [[Cherif Ndiaye]] in advance of the club's [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League]] campaign.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.zurnal.rs/scc/clanak/162414/fudbal/zvezda/bomba-u-ponoC-zvezda-dovela-najskuplje-pojacanje-u-istoriji |title=БОМБА У ПОНОЋ: Звезда довела најскупље појачање у историји |publisher=[[Sportski žurnal]] |language=sr |date=2023-09-04}}</ref> On 9 December, he won a penalty and scored his first goal for Red Star, helping his team gain a 3–1 victory over [[FK Mladost Lučani|Mladost Lučani]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.crvenazvezdafk.com/scc/vest/15737/crvena-zvezda-mladost-3-1-1-1 |title=Црвена звезда - Младост 3:1 (1:1) |language=sr |publisher=Red Star Belgrade |date=2023-12-09 |access-date=2023-12-14}}</ref> Red Star extended their unbeaten home run in the Serbian SuperLiga to 122 games with this victory, setting a world record for the longest unbeaten home run in a domestic league.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.iffhs.com/posts/3239 |title=Crvena Zvezda beat Real Madrid's world record! |publisher=IFFHS |date=2023-12-11 |access-date=2023-12-14}}</ref> On 13 December, he scored his first Champions League goal and assisted another goal from a corner kick in a 3–2 defeat to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.crvenazvezdafk.com/scc/vest/15761/crvena-zvezda-mancester-siti-2-3-0-1 |title=Црвена звезда - Манчестер Сити 2:3 (0:1) |language=sr |publisher=Red Star Belgrade |date=2023-12-13 |access-date=2023-12-14}}</ref> On 21 May 2024, he provided an assist from a corner followed by [[Uroš Spajić]]'s winning goal in the [[2023–24 Serbian Cup]] final against [[FK Vojvodina|Vojvodina]].<ref name="srbcup">{{cite news |url=https://meridiansport.rs/fudbal/uzivo-crvena-zvezda-vojvodina-kup-srbije-finale-prenos-arena-premium/ |title=UŽIVO: Crvena zvezda - Vojvodina |language=sr |publisher=Meridian Sport |date=2024-05-21 |access-date=2024-05-22}}</ref> He was voted SuperLiga Player of the Season for his contributions to Red Star's [[Double (association football)|Double]].<ref name="pots"/>

=== Feyenoord ===
On 2 September 2024, Hwang signed a four-year contract with [[Eredivisie]] club [[Feyenoord]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.feyenoord.com/nl/news/feyenoord-contracteert-ervaren-koreaan-inbeom-hwang-020924 |title=Feyenoord contracteert ervaren Koreaan Inbeom Hwang |publisher=Feyenoord |language=nl |date=2024-09-02 |access-date=2024-09-02}}</ref> He received the club's Player of the Month award after his first month at the club,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.feyenoord.com/nl/news/inbeom-hwang-verkozen-tot-koning-van-de-maand-september-051024 |title=Inbeom Hwang verkozen tot Koning van de Maand september |language=nl |publisher=Feyenoord |date=2024-10-05 |access-date=2025-03-23}}</ref> and was selected for the league's Team of the Month the next month.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://eredivisie.eu/news/fc-twente-is-the-main-supplier-for-the-eredivisie-team-of-the-month-for-october/ |title=FC Twente is the main supplier for the Eredivisie Team of the Month for October |publisher=Eredivisie |date=2024-11-01 |access-date=2025-03-23}}</ref> However, his calf was injured in a [[KNVB Cup]] match against [[MVV Maastricht]] on 17 December, and his playing time was decreased due to an aftereffect after the injury.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.feyenoordpings.nl/in-beom-hwang-baalt-het-is-helaas-onderdeel-van-het-leven/ |title=In-Beom Hwang baalt: "Het is helaas onderdeel van het leven" |language=nl |publisher=FeyenoordPings |date=2025-02-27 |access-date=2025-03-23}}</ref>

==International career==
Hwang played a vital role in leading South Korea to the [[Football at the 2018 Asian Games – Men's tournament|2018 Asian Games]] title.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/09/03/0200000000AEN20180903004400315.html|title=U-23 football team players return to heroes' welcome with Asiad gold|publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]] |date=3 September 2018}}</ref> As a reward, he was discharged from [[Asan Mugunghwa FC|Asan Mugunghwa]] less than halfway through his military service and returned to [[Daejeon Citizen FC|Daejeon Citizen]].<ref name="beom" >{{cite web|url=https://sports.news.naver.com/kfootball/news/read.nhn?oid=144&aid=0000574062 |script-title=ko:눈물 펑펑 황인범 "생일에 조기 전역, 기쁘고 아쉬워…아산·대전 함께 승격하길" [인터뷰&] |trans-title=He was discharged from Asan Mugunghwa early. Because he won the gold medal at the 2018 Asian Games. |publisher=[[Sports Kyunghyang]] |language=ko-kr |date=20 September 2018}}</ref>

Hwang made his senior international debut in September 2018, and later that year, he scored his first senior international goal in a 2–2 friendly home draw against [[Panama national football team|Panama]] on 16 October.<ref name="MLS Profile"/>

In the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]], Hwang showed impressive play and was selected for [[ESPN]]'s Team of the Tournament.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/afc-asian-cup/0/blog/post/3766085/qatars-record-breaking-almoez-ali-leads-asian-cup-team-of-the-tournament |title=Qatar's record-breaking Almoez Ali leads Asian Cup Team of the Tournament |publisher=ESPN |date=3 February 2019 |access-date=14 August 2020}}</ref> He was also named the Most Valuable Player of the [[2019 EAFF E-1 Football Championship|2019 EAFF Championship]] after leading South Korea to the title.<ref name="EAFF2019">{{cite news |url=https://eaff.com/competitions/eaff2019/index.html |title=EAFF E-1 Football Championship 2019 Final Korea Republic |publisher=EAFF |access-date=14 August 2020}}</ref>

Nicknamed the "Bento's crown prince", Hwang was one of South Korean players whom [[Paulo Bento]] trusted most, and he participated in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] as expected. He played all four of South Korea's World Cup matches until the round of 16.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.khan.co.kr/sports/worldcup/article/202212062210005 |script-title=ko:울어버린 '벤투 황태자'…"모든 게 감독님 덕분입니다" |language=ko |publisher=[[Kyunghyang Shinmun]] |date=2022-12-06 |access-date=2023-03-30}}</ref>

Hwang played for the national team under [[Jürgen Klinsmann]] in the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]]. He had a goal and an assist in a victory over [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]], and enticed an opponent to score an own goal in a draw with [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=47415 |script-title=ko:'벤투호의 황태자→클린스만호의 에이스'...황인범, '자책골 유도+최고 평점' 만점 활약 |publisher=FourFourTwo |language=ko |date=2024-01-21 |access-date=2024-02-07}}</ref> He successfully performed his role in the first two group stage matches, but his fans were disappointed with his mistakes responsible for conceding goals to opponents in the other matches. During a 3–3 draw with [[Malaysia national football team|Malaysia]], he lost possession of the ball in front of his team's penalty box and the mistake was followed by opponent's goal.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chosun.com/sports/football/2024/01/26/UTC755WN3FHBAYLVQTSJP73P4A/ |script-title=ko:[카타르 현장인터뷰]'순둥이' 황인범의 분노 "반칙이라고 생각, VAR 결과 바뀌지 않았다!" |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |language=ko |date=2024-01-26 |access-date=2024-02-07}}</ref>

==Style of play==
J.J. Adams of ''The [[National Post]]'' noted that Hwang "can play [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|centrally]] or on the [[Midfielder#Winger|wing]], but thrives as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking mid]] — a [[Midfielder#Box-to-box midfielder|box-to-box]] No. 8. He's known for precision passing, aggressive tackling, possession composure and a willingness to take on defenders with the ball at his feet".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://nationalpost.com/sports/soccer/mls/vancouver-whitecaps/whitecaps-thrilled-to-be-signing-tantalizing-potential-so-hwang-on |title=Whitecaps thrilled to be signing tantalizing potential, so Hwang on |work=The National Post |last=Adams |first=J.J. |date=26 January 2019 |access-date=4 March 2020 }}</ref>

After watching Hwang's performance at Feyenoord, [[Karim El Ahmadi]] stated "Hwang looked around him carefully while turning to the left or right with his two-footed ability. He put his teammates in the right places and distributed plays in front of defense. He also showed good tackles."<ref name="El Ahmadi">{{cite news |url=https://www.fr12.nl/nieuws/el-ahmadi-gevaarlijk-om-te-zeggen-maar-hwang-lijkt-op-ono |title=El Ahmadi: "Gevaarlijk om te zeggen, maar Hwang lijkt op Ono" |language=nl |website=FR12.nl |date=2024-09-22 |access-date=2025-03-29}}</ref> [[Wesley Sneijder]] also paid attention to Hwang's two-footedness, which can make unforeseeable turns. Sneijder thought Hwang had abilities to change games and to see the run of games.<ref name="Sneijder">{{cite news |url=https://www.soccernews.nl/news/sneijder-bewondert-feyenoorder-dit-kun-je-niet-aanleren/ |title=Sneijder bewondert Feyenoorder: 'Dit kun je niet aanleren' |language=nl |website=Soccernews.nl |date=2024-11-07 |access-date=2025-03-29}}</ref> By them, Hwang was compared to [[Shinji Ono]], the former Asian player who helped Feyenoord win the [[2001–02 UEFA Cup]].<ref name="El Ahmadi"/><ref name="Sneijder"/>

